<p><a name="Japanese_era_names" id="Japanese_era_names"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=History_of_Japan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: Japanese era names">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Japanese era names</span></h2>
<div class="rellink noprint relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Japanese_era_name" title="Japanese era name">Japanese era name</a></div>
<p>Era Name (<i><a href="/wiki/Japanese_era_name" title="Japanese era name">Nengō</a></i>) in Japan (after Meiji)</p>
<dl>
<dd><i>Nengō</i> are commonly used in Japan as an alternative to the <a href="/wiki/Gregorian_calendar" title="Gregorian calendar">Gregorian calendar</a>.</dd>
<dd>For example, in censuses, birthdays are written using <i>Nengō</i>.</dd>
<dd>Dates of newspapers and official documents are also written using <i>Nengō</i>.</dd>
<dd><i>Nengō</i> are changed upon the enthronement of each new <a href="/wiki/Japanese_emperor" title="Japanese emperor" class="mw-redirect">Emperor of Japan</a> (<i>Tennō</i>).</dd>
</dl>
<dl>
<dd><a href="/wiki/Meiji_period" title="Meiji period">Meiji</a> (1868 – 1912)</dd>
<dd><a href="/wiki/Taish%C5%8D_period" title="Taishō period">Taishō</a> (1912 – 1925)</dd>
<dd><a href="/wiki/Sh%C5%8Dwa_period" title="Shōwa period">Shōwa</a> (December 25, 1925 – January 6, 1989)</dd>
<dd><a href="/wiki/Heisei" title="Heisei" class="mw-redirect">Heisei</a> (January 7, 1989 – present)</dd>
</dl>
<dl>
<dd>For example&#160;:
<dl>
<dd>1945 was the 20th year of Shōwa.</dd>
<dd>2005 was the 17th year of Heisei.</dd>
<dd>1989 was the 64th year of Shōwa through January 6, but on January 7, it became the 1st year(<i>Gan-nen</i>) of Heisei.</dd>
</dl>
</dd>
</dl>
<dl>
<dd>Before World War II ended, Imperial era (<i><a href="/wiki/K%C5%8Dki" title="Kōki" class="mw-redirect">Kōki</a></i>) is also used in common that the year of enthronement of first emperor (<i>Jimmu-Tennō</i>) is defined as First Year. (= 660 BC)<sup id="cite_ref-23" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-23" title=""><span>[</span>24<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-24" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-24" title=""><span>[</span>25<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-factbook_25-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-factbook-25" title=""><span>[</span>26<span>]</span></a></sup></dd>
</dl>
