<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0004-4687(199407)34%3A7%3C589%3AERIJHI%3E2.0.CO%3B2-6" class="external text" title="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0004-4687(199407)34%3A7%3C589%3AERIJHI%3E2.0.CO%3B2-6" rel="nofollow">Electoral Reform in Japan: How It was Enacted and Changes It May Bring</a>, Raymond V. Christensen, <a href="/wiki/Asian_Survey" title="Asian Survey">Asian Survey</a>, Vol. 34, No. 7, 1994</li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.kobe-jma.go.jp/shiryou/higaijishin/higaijishin.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.kobe-jma.go.jp/shiryou/higaijishin/higaijishin.htm" rel="nofollow">兵庫県の主な被害地震</a>, Kobe Marine Observatory</li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.cfr.org/publication/9238/" class="external text" title="http://www.cfr.org/publication/9238/" rel="nofollow">Aum Shinrikyo (Japan, cultists)</a>, Council on Foreign Relations</li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFNihon_Kokugo_Daijiten_Dai_Nihan_Hensh.C5.AB_Iin_Kai">Nihon Kokugo Daijiten Dai Nihan Henshū Iin Kai (2001-2002) (in Japanese). <i><a href="/wiki/Nihon_Kokugo_Daijiten" title="Nihon Kokugo Daijiten">Nihon Kokugo Daijiten</a>: Volume 5</i>. Tōkyō: <a href="/wiki/Shogakukan" title="Shogakukan">Shōgakukan</a>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/4095210052" class="internal">ISBN 4-095-21005-2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BNihon+Kokugo+Daijiten%5D%5D%3A+Volume+5&amp;rft.aulast=Nihon+Kokugo+Daijiten+Dai+Nihan+Hensh%C5%AB+Iin+Kai&amp;rft.au=Nihon+Kokugo+Daijiten+Dai+Nihan+Hensh%C5%AB+Iin+Kai&amp;rft.date=2001-2002&amp;rft.place=T%C5%8Dky%C5%8D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BShogakukan%7CSh%C5%8Dgakukan%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=4-095-21005-2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_Japan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMatsumura2006">Matsumura, Akira (2006) (in Japanese). <i><a href="/wiki/Daijirin" title="Daijirin">Daijirin</a> (Third Edition)</i>. Tōkyō: <a href="/wiki/Sanseido" title="Sanseido">Sanseidō</a>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/4385139059" class="internal">ISBN 4-385-13905-9</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BDaijirin%5D%5D+%28Third+Edition%29&amp;rft.aulast=Matsumura&amp;rft.aufirst=Akira&amp;rft.au=Matsumura%2C+Akira&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.place=T%C5%8Dky%C5%8D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BSanseido%7CSanseid%C5%8D%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=4-385-13905-9&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_Japan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
